What is an Icon?
Simple definition: A graphical symbol or pictogram used to represent actions, objects, or concepts. Icons are not interactive by themselves (they don't respond to taps).

Think of it like: An emoji or image that conveys meaning without words.

The 3 Most Important Properties
1️⃣ Icons (Which Icon to Show)================================================================
What it does: Specifies which icon to display from the Material Icons library.

dart
Icon(Icons.favorite)  // ❤️ Heart icon
Icon(Icons.search)    // 🔍 Magnifying glass
Icon(Icons.home)      // 🏠 Home icon
Common Icons:

Icon	Code	Usage
❤️	Icons.favorite	Like/Save
🔍	Icons.search	Search
🏠	Icons.home	Home
⚙️	Icons.settings	Settings
📤	Icons.share	Share
🗑️	Icons.delete	Delete
✏️	Icons.edit	Edit
➕	Icons.add	Add
➖	Icons.remove	Remove
✅	Icons.check	Confirm/Success
❌	Icons.close	Close/Cancel
☰	Icons.menu	Menu
←	Icons.arrow_back	Back
→	Icons.arrow_forward	Forward



2️⃣ size (How Big)========================================
What it does: Sets the size of the icon in logical pixels.

dart
Icon(Icons.star, size: 24)   // Small
Icon(Icons.star, size: 48)   // Medium
Icon(Icons.star, size: 72)   // Large
Default: 24.0

3️⃣ color (What Color)======================================
What it does: Sets the color of the icon.

dart
Icon(Icons.favorite, color: Colors.red)     // Red heart
Icon(Icons.favorite, color: Colors.pink)    // Pink heart
Icon(Icons.favorite, color: Colors.white)   // White heart









